reviews.author: Antonio Garc√≠a
reviews.text: This corner of the Lima district of Chorrillos is an almost hidden place in this part of the Peruvian capital. When the beautiful Pedro de Osma avenue takes us to the district boundary between Barranco and Chorrillos, to the right are the streets that access this sector that houses beautiful houses, some from the beginning of the 20th century, including the summer house of former president Billingurst. It is a completely residential area so you will not find anywhere to eat. Ideal for walking and cycling. The view towards the sea is beautiful, you can see, among others, Pescadores beach and Morro Solar. Its approximately 500 meters of route culminate in the old "Chalet" school of the religious of the Sacred Heart.
